    "body": "### Problem\n`nvim --clean -u repro.lua repro.lua`\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, 1, vim.fn.line('.') - 1, 0, {\n  virt_text_pos = 'inline',\n  virt_text = { { 'a\\tb', 'Error' } },\n  -- virt_text = { { 'a' .. (' '):rep(vim.o.tabstop) .. 'b', 'Error' } },\n  -- virt_text = { { 'test', 'Error' } },\n})\nvim.defer_fn(function() vim.api.nvim_input('f($') end, 100)\n```\n\n`<c-l>` can make it redraw correctly, but it will be wrong again when I move cursor.\n\n<img width=\"1578\" height=\"347\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/37f9477d-c9a6-471d-b707-6bac3ed3f06b\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nDisplay correctly.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1457+g183f8cc59d\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuilt from source",
